## How to Use This File

### Marking Tasks Complete
1. Change `[ ]` to `[x]` when task is done
2. Add completion entry to "Task Completion Log"
3. Update progress percentages at top
4. Update context.md with any discoveries

### Adding New Tasks
1. Add to appropriate phase with [NEW] prefix
2. Explain why it wasn't in original plan
3. Update total hours estimate
4. Check if it blocks other tasks

### During Work Sessions
1. Check next uncompleted task
2. Review dependencies
3. Work on task
4. Mark complete when done
5. Update "Last Updated" timestamp

### End of Session
1. Review what was completed
2. Update progress tracking
3. Note any blockers
4. Run `/dev-docs-update` to preserve context

---

## Notes

- Tasks should be marked complete IMMEDIATELY after finishing
- Update context.md with discoveries during each task
- If task takes significantly longer than estimated, note why
- If task becomes unnecessary, strike through and explain why
